1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Bêla temaşevanên ezîz, gelek caran me behsa Çiyayê Lêlûn
kiriye.
 
Dear viewers, we have often talked about Mount Lelun.

2
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Em derbasî herêma Şêrawa bûn. Hîro dîsa me berê xwe daye
herêma Şêrawa, Çiyayê Lêlûn.
 
We passed into the Sherawa region. Today again we have
headed to the Sherawa region, Mount Lelun.

3
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Vê carê jî em derbasî gundê Bı'yê (Ba'yê / Be'yê) bûne. Em
dixwazin hinekî urf û adetên vî gundî nas bikin.
 
This time too we have entered the village of Bê'yê. We want
to get to know some of the customs and traditions of this
village.

4
00:00:43,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Çawa vê gundê jiyan dike? Em hevdu nas bikin, bi hev ra
biaxivin. Vê hefteyê jî em li gundê Bê'yê ne.
 
How does this village live? Let's get to know each other,
talk with each other. This week too we are in the village of
Bê'yê.

5
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Merheba stêra.
 
Hello star.

6
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Ehlan we sehlan keko, xêr hatî ser çava.
 
Welcome brother, welcome, upon my eyes.

7
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Sax bî, apê Cemal, me xwest hinekî destpêkê da em hinekî
dîroka gundê we bipirsin.
 
May you be healthy, Uncle Cemal, we wanted to first ask a
bit about the history of your village.

8
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Dîroka Bê'yê, ev gundê we çend sal dachiye?
 
The history of Bê'yê, how many years old is this village of
yours?

9
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Welleh, pir salan dachiye. Pir zeman da dachiye.
 
By God, it was built many years ago. It was built a long
time ago.

10
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Bes 200 sal û vir da em gundê xwe nas dikin.
 
But we have known our village for the last 200 years.

11
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Berê malê Şêxo Nebo li vir bûn, û malek din jî malê Elûşê
Elî Hesen.
 
Before, the family of Shexo Nebo were here, and another
family, the family of Alush Ali Hasan.

12
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Û em jî ji Tofê û Sicê hatin vederê, û em li hev hewiyan.
 
And we too came here from Tof and Sij, and we gathered
together.

13
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Û civakî me pir xweş bû ji wî wextî da heta nuka.
 
And our society was very nice from that time until now.

14
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Û em giştî yek in, tebayî yek in, û hezkirina me zêde pir e,
maşelleh, û rewşa me pir xweş e.
 
And we are all one, our agreement is one, and our love is
very abundant, Masha'Allah, and our situation is very nice.

15
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Navê gundê we destpêkê da Bê'yê ye, lê navekî din lê ne-
 
The name of your village originally is Bê'yê, but did it
have another name-

16
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Na, navê gundê me destpêkê da ne Bê'yê bû, ji bo
 
No, the name of our village at first wasn't Bê'yê, because

17
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Hikumeta nîzam qulipand, bûn hukmê dîktatorî hatin, vêrê
navê gundan giştî xera kirin, Ba'î.
 
The government changed the system, they became a dictatorial
rule, they came here and ruined all the village names,
[making it] Ba'i.

18
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Bes berê navê gundê me Ba bû.
 
But before the name of our village was Ba. (Bê)

19
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Ser Bê ye, ba yekî xurt e yanî navê wî Bê bû.
 
It's on Bê, the wind is strong meaning its name was Bê.

20
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Û her wiha lê hatî bû hukmeta ku li vir ketî di navê xwe
nedanûne kî derê.
 
And also the government that entered here didn't leave any
[Kurdish] names anywhere.

21
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Navê kurdî nane. Ji Bê hatiye.
 
It doesn't leave Kurdish names. It comes from Bê.

22
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Ji ber ku gelek gundên me li vir hene ji navê Bê hatiye.
 
Because many of our villages here come from the name Bê.

23
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Yanî mînak bibêjim, wek gundê Basûfanê, Basûlê, Basûtê...
 
I mean, to give an example, like the village of Basufan,
Basul, Basut...

24
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Ev navna hemî ji Bê hatine. Yanî gundê we jî ji Bê hatiye?
 
All these names come from Bê. So your village also comes
from Bê?

25
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Ji Bê hatiye, ev navê nuka dibêjin 'Ba'î' erebî ne, ne Ba'î
ye.
 
It comes from Bê, this name they say now 'Ba'i' is Arabic,
no, it's not Ba'i.

26
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Ji Bê hatiye. Navê xwe yê esasî ew e.
 
It comes from Bê. Its original name is that.

27
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Ji ber ku ev jî deşta... Çiyayê Lêlûn e.
 
Because this is also the plain... Mount Lelun.

28
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Û li ser Çiyayê Lêlûnê jî bayê xurt... yanî zivistanan.
 
And on Mount Lelun too, the strong wind... I mean in
winters.

29
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Werê ye, temamî te divê jî, bayê xwe pir zêde heye û esasê
xwe ser Bê ye yanî.
 
That's right, exactly as you say, its wind is very strong
and its essence is based on Bê, you see.

30
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Ne Ba'î ye. Bê.
 
It's not Ba'i. Bê.

31
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Yanî ev destpêkê da ev gund heye. Binavkirina wî Bê ye?
 
So this village has been here since the beginning. Its
naming is Bê?

32
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:59,000
Binavkirina wî ketî bû tabi evê navê ketî bû. Evê navê wî Bê
bû.
 
Its naming had occurred, naturally this name had occurred.
This name was Bê.

33
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Navê wî Bê. Erê.
 
Its name is Bê. Yes.

34
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Beriya miletê vir da jiyan dikî kî bûn?
 
Before, who were the people living here?

35
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:08,000
Beriya miletê vir da, ji 200 sal û vir da em zanin, ji wê da
em nizanin.
 
Before the people here, we have known for the last 200
years, before that we don't know.

36
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Beriya em... Ev gunda, ê Basûfanê bû.
 
Before we... This village belonged to Basufan.

37
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:16,000
Ji gulê hikumet hatê da, ji hev fasil bûn, kirine Ba'î, bes
navê gundî me bi xwe Bê ye.
 
Since the government came, they were separated from each
other, they made it Ba'i, but our village's name itself is
Bê.

38
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Bes tabi'ê Basûfanê bû.
 
But it was dependent on Basufan.

39
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Û paşê weha milet hat lê kom bûn, gundî malê tew... taîfa
malê Şêxo Nebo û malê Elûş, malê Misto û Mehmûd gî hatin.
 
And then people came and gathered here, villagers, the
family of... the sect of the family of Shexo Nebo and the
family of Alush, the family of Misto and Mahmud all came.

40
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Lê civiya kirin tebeviyek, rûniştin û jiyan û rewşa me pir
xweş e, û cîrantiya me pir xweş e.
 
They gathered here and made a community, sat and lived, and
our situation is very good, and our neighborliness is very
good.

41
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Gelek edet û dînî yanî... Ewna Zerdeştî ne, em Misilman in,
tefrîqe me ko tune.
 
Many customs and religions... They are Zoroastrians, we are
Muslims, we have no separation.

42
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Mirovî dimira te nizanî kî xwediyê xwe ya, mek xizmeta hev
dikirin, pir me hevdû... alîkar dikirin.
 
Someone would die, you wouldn't know who their owner is, we
would serve each other, we would help each other a lot.

43
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Rewşa me yê eskeriya ya, alîkar dikin giştiya hevda.
 
Our military situation, they all help each other.

44
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:50,000
Gî alîkariya gundî me pir xweş e û pir delal e. Pir
hezkirinik mezin tê da heye.
 
All the help in our village is very nice and very lovely.
There is a great love in it.

45
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Bi xwe tu ji kîjan malbatê yî?
 
From which family are you yourself?

46
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Ez bi xwe ji malbata malê Mistoma.
 
I am myself from the family of the family of Misto.

47
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:58,000
Û malbata din te got malê Elûş û malê Şêx Nebo.
 
And the other family you said the family of Alush and the
family of Shex Nebo.

48
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Malê Şêx Nebo, malê Elûş hene, sê malbat in na?
 
The family of Shex Nebo, there is the family of Alush, they
are three families, right?

49
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Ev malbatên dîn jî berê li vir bûn?
 
Were these other families also here before?

50
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Erê, berê li vir in.
 
Yes, they have been here since before.

51
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Hûn ji ku derê hatine?
 
Where did you come from?

52
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Em ji Tofê û Sicê hatin.
 
We came from Tof and Sij.

53
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Sicê te zane ku der e? Tê caran çûyê?
 
Do you know where Sij is? Have you ever been there?

54
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Na na, neçûme caran wila.
 
No no, I've never been there, by God.

55
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Wa bi xwe nizanim jî li ku ye, bes ez ... kalê me mirî
digot, digot em ji Tofê û Sicê hatin.
 
I don't even know where it is myself, but I... our dead
grandfather used to say, he said we came from Tof and Sij.

56
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Ev gundek heye, li hemberî Şiyê ye.
 
There is a village, it's opposite Shiye.

57
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Hema li ser xetê dikeve, te dît. Piranî ew gund û gundên
navçeya Şiyê va...
 
It lies right on the border, you see. Mostly that village
and the villages of the Shiye district...

58
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Mirovê hevin, meriyê hev in. Ew têkiliyên wan teva bi hev
girtiye.
 
They are relatives, they are related to each other. All
their relations are connected.

59
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Yanî gundek gelek nêzîk e yanî ne dûr yanî.
 
I mean it's a very close village, I mean not far, you know.

60
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Erê heval, gelek nêzîk e, bes ez nizanim bi deqîqet li wî
derê.
 
Yes friend, it's very close, but I don't know exactly where
it is.

61
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Nuka em pir kêfxweş bûn, em eşîra em li wî derê, hedûdê berê
tina bû, kî ku da diçû, wî da li wî derê dima.
 
Now we are very happy, we tribes we are there, there was no
border before, whoever went anywhere, they stayed there.

62
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Demek ku Tirkî hidûd danî, we fasilê jî em da... her kîkî
aliyekî ma, wekî yekî bû.
 
When Turkey set the border, with that separation we...
everyone stayed on one side, it became like that.

63
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Naha gundê we çend xanî tê de heye?
 
Now how many houses does your village have in it?

64
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Welleh, nêzîka 150 xanî tê da heye.
 
By God, there are about 150 houses in it.

65
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:59,000
150 tê de heye û... e... ekîd tê da heye, 150 heye.
 
There are 150 in it and... uh... certainly there are in it,
there are 150.

66
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Erê. Naha gundê we jî... gundê herî dawî ye, yê... ji Efrînê
ye.
 
Yes. Now your village too... is the last village, of...
Afrin.

67
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,000
Basûfan heye. Piştî wê zate Keleha Sem'anê tê.
 
Basufan is there. After that, already the Citadel of Simeon
comes.

68
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Erê, Keleha Sem'anê. Bi xwe o meye.
 
Yes, the Citadel of Simeon. In itself it's ours.

69
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Yanî, ji zeman da da ev meye.
 
I mean, since ancient times, this has been ours.

70
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Çi heta nuka... birîne.
 
Only until now... they've cut it off.

71
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:22,000
Wan çetan jî înşelleh wê zû ji hev herin, em me xema wan
naxin, tu mişkile wan tune.
 
Those gangs too, God willing, will soon disperse from each
other, we don't worry about them, there's no problem with
them.

72
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Am... nuka em li vê derê sekiniyene, rewşa me pir xweş e,
mişkila me çê nabe.
 
We... now we are settled here, our situation is very nice,
we have no problems.

73
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Inşelleh em ê bibin û emê herin a wan ê derkevin herin, ewên
maf xwarin in, em bi maf in.
 
God willing we will go and they will leave and go away, they
are usurpers, we are rightful.

74
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Tiştê din li vê derê cihê me heye... ziyaretek heye,
 
Another thing, we have a place here... there is a shrine,

75
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Navê xwe 'Wesilqerar' e, wekî 'Murasil Ereb' digotin berê,
we navê 'Risaleya' diçû, navê xwe 'Wesilqerar' e.
 
Its name is 'Wasilqarar', like they used to say 'Murasil
Arab' before, it went by the name 'Risaleya', its name is
'Wasilqarar'.

76
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Dîrokî, kevneşop... em pir kevn e. Miletê me yê kurd zêde
kevn e li vê derê ye.
 
Historical, traditional... we are very ancient. Our Kurdish
people are very ancient here.

77
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,000
Yanî pir salan da li vir hene.
 
I mean they have been here for many years.

78
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Naha wek gundê Bê'yê, kanî tê de hene?
 
Now like the village of Bê'yê, are there springs in it?

79
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Kaniyên xwe tinene heval, bîrên terwazê sê çor bîr tê de
hene, û ava xwe jî pirin da ketiye dehîfe.
 
It doesn't have its own springs friend, there are three or
four artesian wells in it, and its water has also mostly
decreased, it's weak.

80
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:04,000
Yanî ava wan... sibê heta êvarî belkî du siware ti rav
dirixê... dikişê daba...
 
I mean their water... from morning to evening maybe two...
it draws two buckets in total... it pulls down...

81
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Kaniyên tê tune ne. Û bîrên me hene, me bîr kolane.
 
There are no springs in it. And we have wells, we have dug
wells.

82
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:12,000
Ew ji zeman da da kalê me jî mere kolan, me jî henek kolan.
 
Since ancient times our grandfathers also dug them for us,
we also dug some.

83
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,000
Em bi avê sûra tînin boşî dikin, û em dikişînin û em bi avê
dixin.
 
We bring water from the tanks to fill them, and we draw it
and we use it for water.

84
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Kaniyên vir tune.
 
There are no springs here.

85
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Berê we av ji ku dianî?
 
Before, where did you bring water from?

86
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Berê welleh... pir zor bû, me diçû av ji Xezîwê dianî.
 
Before, by God... it was very hard, we went and brought
water from Khaziwa.

87
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,000
Kaniyek Xezîwê heye, derdikeve.
 
There is a spring in Khaziwa, it comes out.

88
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Me av ji wira dianî, vê derê berbangê radibûn.
 
We brought water from there, here they would get up at dawn.

89
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Bi devê... we ramedihêçûn... me av dianî dihat.
 
With the mouth... we would manage... we would bring water
and come.

90
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:33,000
Yanî pir zor, pir zehmet bû ser me.
 
I mean very hard, it was very difficult for us.

91
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:37,000
Rûyê dina qal dikişandin, berbanga dikişandin, nişkana qal
dikişandin.
 
They used to haul holes during the day, they used to haul at
dawn, they used to haul holes at noon.

92
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:42,000
Bi tenekeya ya ye, du teneke tanî, ye heye çar tanîn, yanî
pir zor, zehmet bû.
 
It was with a tin, bringing two tins, there is one bringing
four, I mean very hard, it was difficult.

93
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Û elhemdulîlah, nuka pir xweş e û em pir kêfxweş in.
 
And praise be to God, now it's very nice and we are very
happy.

94
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:53,000
Hewe zamana, zemanekî rehet bû nuka, pir delale pir xweşe,
zamaniyek xweşî oy e, wa'î ye, pêşketiye...
 
That time, it's a comfortable time now, it's very lovely
very nice, it's a pleasant time, aware, developed...

95
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Heval, cima'eta me hene, tirsî me tune ne.
 
Friend, we have our people, we have no fear.

96
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Em tiştkî, bixwazin dalebî me dimaşe.
 
We want something, our request is processed.

97
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:05,000
Em çi bixwazin, yanî mubakerî işê me dimeşe. Zora me tine ye
de işkî, mişkila me tine ye.
 
Whatever we want, I mean our work proceeds smoothly. We
don't have any difficulty with any work, we have no
problems.

98
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,000
Xwedê bike, masiyek wana de. Gelek spas.
 
May God make it so, no problem with them. Thank you very
much.

99
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Mîyt ehlen wesehlen, hev al, serçava ... xêr wuslemet hatin.
Ehlen wesehlen, serkeftin ji we ra.
 
A hundred welcomes, friend, upon the eyes... you came with
goodness and safety. Welcome, success to you.

100
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Gundê Be'yê grêdayî navçeya Şêrawa ya Kantona Efrînê, 22
kîlometreyî li başûrê bajarê Efrînê,
 
The village of Be'ye, affiliated with the Sherawa district
of the Afrin Canton, is 22 kilometers south of the city of
Afrin,

101
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:45,000
û 10 kîlometreyî li başûrê bajarokê Basûtê dikeve.
 
and 10 kilometers south of the town of Basute.

102
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Navê gund weke tê texmînkirin ji ristaba hey hatî, ji ber ku
li ser bilindahiyên Çiyayê Lêlûnê hatiye avakirin.
 
The name of the village, as it is estimated, comes from the
strong wind, because it is built on the heights of Mount
Lelun.

103
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Û bayê wê devarê gelek e.
 
And the wind in that area is abundant.

104
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Gundê Bê'yê wekî gundekî biçûk e, berê.
 
The village of Be'ye is like a small village, originally.

105
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Bi navê gundê girêdayî gundê Basûfanê bû. Lê piştre mezin bû
û gundek serbixwe.
 
By name, the village was dependent on the village of
Basufan. But later it grew and became an independent
village.

106
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:12,000
Li ew ma bî'ê ne ketiye mare, ango temenê wê ne bihtirî 150
salî ye.
 
To that... it hasn't fallen to us, meaning its age is not
more than 150 years.

107
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:19,000
Xerabe ne bû ko êzîdî bû, yekemîn kes ji gundê Basûfanê hat
û li vir rûniştici bû.
 
It was not ruins, it was Yezidi, the first person came from
the village of Basufan and settled here.

108
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:24,000
Piştre qerehesokê ko xwe misilman e, ew jî hat û li vir
rûniştici bû.
 
Then a Qara Hasok, who is a Muslim, he also came and settled
here.

109
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Bi vî awayî gundê Be'yê bi du pêkhatayan êzîdî û misilman
pêk tê.
 
In this way, the village of Be'ye consists of two
components, Yezidi and Muslim.

110
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:34,000
Û hemû di nava yekîtiyeke germ û xweş de dijîn.
 
And all live in a warm and pleasant unity.

111
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:39,000
Derdora 140 xanî û nêzî hezar kes li gund dijîn.
 
Around 140 houses and nearly a thousand people live in the
village.

112
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:59,000
Û her du pêkhatiyên êzîdî û misilman in.
 
And both are components of Yezidi and Muslim.

113
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,000
Merheba stêra dayê.
 
Hello star mother.

114
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:22,000
Ehlan we sehlan, ev ha sarçava, xêr we silamet.
 
Welcome, upon the eyes, goodness and safety.

115
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:28,000
Sax bî dayê. Em ê di gundê Be'yê da behsa teniyê kin. Me jî
meraq kir em derbasî hem te bûn.
 
May you be healthy mother. We will talk about weaving in the
village of Be'ye. We were curious too, so we dropped by you.

116
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,000
E destpêkê em tenûrekî nas bikin.
 
First, let's get to know a tandoor.

117
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,000
Ez Elîf Mistefama.
 
I am Elif Mistefa.

118
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Navê Mistefa. Evê me ye?
 
The name of Mistefa. Is this ours?

119
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,000
Serçava.
 
Upon the eyes.

120
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,000
Tu bi xwe gundê Be'yê ye an ji gundê din ye?
 
Are you yourself from the village of Be'ye or from another
village?

121
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:40,000
Welleh, ez bûka Bê'yê me, ez ji Basfanê me.
 
By God, I am a bride of Bê'ye, I am from Basfan.

122
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,000
Cîranê hev in?
 
You are neighbors?

123
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

124
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Tu êzidî ye?
 
Are you Yezidi?

125
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,000
Hî.
 
Yes.

126
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,000
Ser çavê min.
 
Upon my eyes.

127
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Ê dayê, ev çend sal in tu di vî gundî-
 
Mother, how many years have you been in this village-

128
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,000
Çend sal e?
 
How many years?

129
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Tu bi xwe çend sal in di vî gundê?
 
How many years have you yourself been in this village?

130
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,000
Wekî 40-50 salek dibiya.
 
It must be about 40-50 years.

131
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:58,000
Yanî piştî tu derbasî gundê Be'yê bû, te dest bi tenî-
 
I mean, after you entered the village of Be'ye, you started
to weave-

132
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,000
Erê, erê.
 
Yes, yes.

133
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:01,000
Kê ev malbatê te re... teniyê diyare kî?
 
Who for you in this family... weaving is clearly who?

134
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:04,000
Ê min destpê kir di nav eqrebeyê xwe, xwişk û xalan.
 
I started among my relatives, sisters and aunts.

135
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,000
Min qumaşê fîstanê xwe danî erdê.
 
I put the fabric of my dress on the ground.

136
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:11,000
Û min ji xwere qumaş anî, min qes da pîya kir dirût.
 
And I brought myself fabric, I cut the legs and sewed them.

137
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:15,000
Û min qesda şidre kir dirût, û min qesda çepkan kir dirût...
 
And I cut the chest and sewed it, and I cut the arms and
sewed them...

138
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,000
Min gî qut kir û min ji xwere rûnişt û dirût.
 
I cut everything out and I sat down and sewed.

139
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:22,000
Ê kê didirût di gund de? Ji te pêve kî didirût?
 
And who used to sew in the village? Who sewed besides you?

140
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:25,000
Erê, terzî hebû... Jina mixtêr, Helîmê didirût.
 
Yes, there were tailors... The mukhtar's wife, Helîm, used
to sew.

141
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Û jinkek din hebû malbata wê hebû wê didirût.
 
And there was another woman who had a family, she used to
sew.

142
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,000
Yanî piraniya gund, te ji wan re didirût?
 
So you sewed for most of the village?

143
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

144
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,000
Û gundên dorbêlî... kes hebû didirût?
 
And the surrounding villages... was there anyone sewing?

145
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Na, kesî nedidirût.
 
No, no one sewed.

146
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,000
Te tenê?
 
Just you?

147
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Em.
 
Yeah.

148
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,000
Çend sale tu dirûnê dikî?
 
How many years have you been sewing?

149
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,000
Çil sal e ez dirûnê dikim.
 
I've been sewing for forty years.

150
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Yanî emrê te ha?
 
So, all your life, huh?

151
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,000
Çil sal. Erê.
 
Forty years. Yes.

152
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,000
Bê vî makîneyê?
 
Without this machine?

153
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,000
Bi vî makîneyê.
 
With this machine.

154
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:48,000
Yanî te tu carî bi haşetê kehrebê (elektirîkê) alavekî
(makîneyekî) din nebû, yanê?
 
So you never had an electric machine, another machine, I
mean?

155
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,000
Na, hemî bi linga ye.
 
No, it's all with the foot (pedal).

156
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,000
Ew jî bi lingên xwe yê.
 
And that's with your own feet.

157
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,000
Nav van çil salan de, li gund, e... berê hinek din hebûn.
 
In these forty years, in the village, uh... there used to be
some others.

158
00:10:55,000 --> 00:11:00,000
Berê wê, wextê rahalê min ê destê, bavê min ji min re kirî.
 
Before that, my first hand machine, my father bought it for
me.

159
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:03,000
Go meraqê qîza min li ser dirûnê ye, go ez ê ji wan re
dirûnek bikim.
 
He said my daughter is interested in sewing, he said I will
get a sewing machine for her.

160
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:09,000
Paşê ew bû, min ewne firot, û min ve hanî kir.
 
Then it became like that, I sold that one, and I bought this
one.

161
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:13,000
Bêriyê dema ku tiştek, gundiyan dît, ev makîne te kirî...
 
Earlier when the villagers saw that you bought this
machine...

162
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,000
Ê, rahalê min re bavê min kirî.
 
Well, my father bought my first one.

163
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,000
Dît gotin: "Bavo we çi kir, me makîneyek jî bîbana li
malan..."
 
Did they see and say: "Oh my, look what they did, I wish we
had a machine at home too..."

164
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Ê we, na rehmetîyo.
 
Yes, God bless you.

165
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:27,000
Berîya te dît, emrê te terzîyê pêre derbûne li bajar an li
gundan... Terzî tiştek çawan bû?
 
Before, you saw, all your life you worked as a tailor in the
city or the villages... What was it like being a tailor?

166
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:37,000
Çi bima? Wexta ez li cem mala bavê xwe keçik... min sîdrîya
bavê xwe qetand, û min ji xwakê xwe re kir fîstan.
 
What would it be? When I was a young girl at my father's
house... I cut my father's shirt, and I made a dress for my
sister.

167
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Ê bavê min hat, go: "Xêr e? Te fîstanê te xêr e, te sîdrîya
min qetandiye?"
 
Then my father came and said: "What's this? What's going on
with your dress, why did you cut my shirt?"

168
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:46,000
Go: "Te tiştek waha ji min re kira, min bixwesta."
 
She said: "If you had done something like this for me, I
would have wanted it."

169
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:49,000
Çima min sidrîyê wî qetandibû.
 
Why did I cut his shirt?

170
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:56,000
Ê min kir serê xwe, min go: "Ser vê kutekê de, yazê bibim
terzîyek, yan ez ê wê kutekê ji bîr bikim." Min ji bîr
nekir.
 
So I put it in my head, I said: "After this beating, either
I will become a tailor, or I will forget that beating." I
didn't forget.

171
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,000
Bavê te xwaş e, yan wefat bûye?
 
Is your father alive, or has he passed away?

172
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Xwaş e aboo... betal e, bas faniye. (Wefat bûye)
 
He's fine oh... he's gone, life is fleeting. (He passed
away)

173
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,000
Seet xwaş!
 
God bless!

174
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:08,000
Ê dayê, kanî em piçekî li ser behsa fîstanê... cilê kurdî...
kirasê kurdî... tu didirûtî?
 
So mother, let's talk a little bit about the dress...
Kurdish clothes... Kurdish dress... did you sew them?

175
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
Eh.
 
Yes.

176
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:13,000
Ê ka, kîjan te bêtir didirût, e, taybetiya Efrînê, cil û
bergê Efrînê te didirûtî?
 
Which ones did you sew the most, the specific ones of Afrin,
did you sew the clothes of Afrin?

177
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,000
Dewra Efrînê, ez ê şerawliya gî didirût.
 
In the Afrin area, I sewed all the Shera style clothes.

178
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:23,000
Na ez qesda wê dikim, ku... evên tu dirûnê dikî, evên ku tu
ji derveyî yên Efrînê dibînî, hemo dayikên me dibînin ku
cilên wan taybet e, yên Efrînê ne...
 
No, I mean that... the ones you sew, the ones you see
outside of Afrin, all our mothers see that their clothes are
special, they are from Afrin...

179
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,000
Dema ku tu diçî Cizîrê, taybetiya Cizîrê hene...
 
When you go to Cizire, there is a Cizire specialty...

180
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,000
Eh we jî... az wan jî didirût.
 
Yeah, that too... I used to sew those too.

181
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,000
Yanî ew çar parçe Kurdistanê... te hemû dirût?
 
So the four parts of Kurdistan... you sewed them all?

182
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

183
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,000
Êşê Şerq re jî wan jî te didirût?
 
The clothes from the East too, you used to sew them?

184
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,000
Ê, yên Şerqê re jwan jî didirût.
 
Yes, I used to sew the clothes from the East too.

185
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,000
Yanî te giş didirûtî.
 
So you sewed everything.

186
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:38,000
Erê. Lê ev li ber çavê min hemî yên Efrînê ne li ber min.
 
Yes. But these in front of me are all from Afrin.

187
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,000
Bes yên Şerqê re jî ez didirût.
 
But I also sewed the clothes from the East.

188
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:43,000
Heya we dirûtîye an we xwe re jî emil heye?
 
Have you sewed them or do you have work for yourself too?

189
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:47,000
Yanî ez vê... milletek maye Cizîrê? Ê cilê wan jî xwaşik
in...
 
So I... a nation remains in Cizire? Their clothes are
beautiful too...

190
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,000
Erê. Ez ji wan jî hez dikim.
 
Yes. I like those too.

191
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:58,000
Min go, meraqa min li ser wan jî heye... min ji pir kesa re
dirûye... û min xwe ra jî yek dirû, ez meraq dikim ez ê roja
Newrozê de derêm ez ê li xwe bikim.
 
I said, I'm interested in those too... I sewed for many
people... and I sewed one for myself too, I'm excited to go
out on Newroz day and wear it.

192
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Ê, ka... em li kî... tu...
 
And, so... where... you...

193
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Te got ez terzî me... Ji kuderê tên cem te?
 
You said you are a tailor... Where do they come to you from?

194
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:08,000
An jî ji kîjan gundan hatin cem te? Ê jin yanî...
 
Or which villages did they come to you from? I mean the
women...

195
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Ji Kibarşînê tên... fafir pê de tên... Beradê tên...
Biçhêderê tên... Xezewîyê tên...
 
They come from Kibarşîn... they come from the other side...
from Berad... from Biçhêder... from Xezewiyê...

196
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,000
Kî navê min dibihîst, ji kuderê dihatin, yani hemî...
 
Whoever heard my name, they came from everywhere, I mean all
of them...

197
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Qumaşekî vedikirin na fîstanekî xwe ji min re dihanîn... û
ez dikarim, ku qeysek jwan re nebim...
 
They would open a fabric or bring me a dress of theirs...
and I could do it without even taking a measurement...

198
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,000
E ma tu li gor bedena wan didirû û tu didirût?
 
So did you sew according to their body measurements and you
sewed it?

199
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,000
E. Belê.
 
Yeah. Yes.

200
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Ê dayê, dema berê, dayikên we... çi li xwe dikirin?
 
So mother, in the old days, your mothers... what did they
wear?

201
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:34,000
Cilên wan te dît? Her herêmekî cilên wan hene...
 
Did you see their clothes? Every region has its own
clothes...

202
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,000
Cilên wan jî, navên wan hene.
 
Their clothes also, they have names.

203
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:40,000
E, ev çine na? Ev Şêrewa û Efrînê gî hemî yekin lê cihê ne?
Ferq herne?
 
Yeah, what are these? Are the ones from Şêrewa and Afrin all
the same but different? Is there a difference?

204
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,000
Hemî yekin, ya Efrînê û yên Şêrewa... Herî.
 
They are all the same, the ones from Afrin and Şêrewa...
Yes.

205
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Bê van re dibêjin...
 
What do they call these...

206
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:48,000
Yên cilên Efrînê Kurmancî... ez... ez li cêf...
 
The Kurdish clothes from Afrin... I... I like them...

207
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,000
Ez cêf.
 
I like.

208
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:55,000
A. Û bi van ra jî dibêjin, ha vî jî me dirûye, ha vî jî bi
van ra jî dibêjin, ha ne...
 
Yes. And they call these too, look I sewed this too, look
they call these too, these...

209
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:58,000
Ev jî ê Efrînê, li xwe dikin, ev, bajêr...
 
This is also from Afrin, they wear it, this, city...

210
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Ha.
 
Ah.

211
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Ho nekin. Ev şêrewa li xwe dikin, ev wan jî?
 
Don't do it like that. The people of Şêrewa wear this, and
them too?

212
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,000
Xwe dikin arê... Çima divên ev weke yên Efrîn e...
 
They wear it yes... Because they say this is like the ones
from Afrin...

213
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,000
Ha!
 
Aha!

214
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,000
Yanî hin Şêrewa li xwe dikir, hin yên Efrînê li xwe dikir...
 
I mean some of the people of Şêrewa wore it, some of the
people of Afrin wore it...

215
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
Hev jê asan e...
 
They are easy...

216
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:23,000
Na, taybet... dema tu derbasî Efrîn dibî, te vî cilî
nedidît. Ya rastî ez pirr gerriyam, bêtir li Kobanî, li
Cizîrê, li Bakurê Kurdistanê as pirr gerriyam... min ti
deran tiştên hanî Efrînê xwe dît evan e?
 
No, it's specific... when you enter Afrin, you didn't see
this dress. Honestly I traveled a lot, more in Kobani, in
Cizire, in Northern Kurdistan I traveled a lot... I haven't
seen things like this Afrin dress anywhere else?

217
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,000
Belê... e.
 
Yes... yeah.

218
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:29,000
Bêqî, tu carekî derketî derveyî Efrînê jî? Tu carî negeşt
xwarê te çûyî gerîyaye?
 
Besides that, did you ever go outside of Afrin? Have you
ever traveled down?

219
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:36,000
Na, Şerqla neçûme, nan, bes Efrîn, bes çûme Tirkiyê û
hatime, ez wek der neketime çu deran.
 
No, I didn't go to Şerqla (Eastern regions), no, just Afrin,
I only went to Turkey and came back, I didn't go out
anywhere else.

220
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,000
Ê ko, innekê ji me ra behsa cilan...
 
So, tell us a bit about the clothes...

221
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Ê, dayikên we çi li xwe dikirin?
 
What did your mothers wear?

222
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:46,000
Yani te dît.. ew te got destmala enîyê ber enîya... wisa
nizanim çi... Kînekê ji me re bêje.
 
I mean you saw... you mentioned the forehead scarf on the
forehead... like that I don't know what... Tell us a little
bit.

223
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:49,000
Merkezî pê da dikirin...
 
They used to tie a "merkezî" around it...

224
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Û paşê diftilîn... Fîstanê Kurmancî li xwe dikirin ev
fîstanê 'ezcêf'...
 
And then they would wrap it... They wore the Kurdish dress,
this 'ezcêf' dress...

225
00:14:54,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Û şal hebûn, ew ber henyê, didanê... Û ev.
 
And there were shawls, they put them on the forehead... And
this.

226
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Şêrewa li xwe dikirin.
 
The people of Şêrewa used to wear it.

227
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Ez ê niho ko jî wê ra... cilê Efrînê ez keçkê kîm... û jer
berhenîya grê dim... û merkezît pê da kîm, û ez ji wer ra
bêjim we ku em şêrewa vî li xwe dikin.
 
Right now, I will... dress a girl in Afrin clothes... and I
will tie a forehead scarf on her... and I'll tie the
merkezî, and I will show you how we in Şêrewa wear this.

228
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:22,000
(Music playing)
 
(Music playing)

229
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,000
Belê temaşevanen hêja, neha jî sê keçik hatin.
 
Yes dear viewers, now three girls have come.

230
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:30,000
Wan jî bi cilên xwe, bi taybet ên Efrînê li xwe kirin... Em
hevdî ji nasbikin.
 
They are also wearing their clothes, especially the ones
from Afrin... Let's get to know each other.

231
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:33,000
Dayê, kanî ji me re bêje, yek êk bêje.
 
Mother, tell us, tell us one by one.

232
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:37,000
Evana, berê dayikên me hane li xwe dikirin.
 
These, our mothers used to wear them like this in the past.

233
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Kincên 'ezcêf' li xwe dikirin, ev jî merkezî didan serê xwe,
û ev jî şalê berheniya.
 
They wore the 'ezcêf' clothes, and they put the 'merkezî' on
their heads, and this is the forehead shawl.

234
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:46,000
Efrînê şêra we hemî li xwe dikirin. Berê...
 
The people of Afrin and Şêrewa all wore it. In the past...

235
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,000
Bli... belê efrîn da we digotin... destmala ber eniya?
 
Right... so in Afrin you used to call it... forehead
handkerchief?

236
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:54,000
Em dibêjin şal, şeraw dibêjin şal... ma em vêra jî dibêjin
merkezîd.
 
We call it a shawl, the people of Şêrewa call it a shawl...
but we also call this 'merkezîd'.

237
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Û ev jê çaw reş ne... Û ev jê çaw reş e, fîstanê Kurmancî û
fîstanê...
 
And this is black cloth... And this is also black cloth, the
Kurdish dress and the dress...

238
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,000
Fîstanê Kurmancî... te dirût?
 
The Kurdish dress... did you sew it?

239
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Kurmancî, ez xwa dikim, berê, dayikê me, hav li xwe dikirin.
 
The Kurdish one, I wear it myself, in the past, our mothers
used to wear it.

240
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:07,000
Û niho ko jî, em jbîr nakin. Înşallah em şopê wan diajon.
Amî...
 
And even now, we don't forget it. God willing, we follow in
their footsteps. Amen...

241
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Yanê keşkê va jî xwe dikin hane?
 
So the girls wear this too, right?

242
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,000
Lê xwe dikin.
 
They wear it.

243
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,000
Bêli.
 
Yes.

244
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,000
Em navê keşkê ve pirsîn. Navê we bi xêr?
 
Let's ask the girls' names. Your name, please?

245
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,000
Colya.
 
Colya.

246
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,000
Fatma.
 
Fatma.

247
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,000
Cînat.
 
Cînat.

248
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,000
Ser çavê min.
 
Welcome.

249
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:21,000
Ê bi vê rengî bû, û ha ye naha jî dewam dikin... Pê rêsî ya,
tiyaxî didin meşin yanî.
 
So it was like this, and it still continues... With
spinning, they keep it going.

250
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,000
Belê, arê.
 
Yes, yeah.

251
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:25,000
Ev cilê wan e... Dema ku hûn diçin kwîceyî we tê nas kirin
em ha?
 
These are their clothes... When you go to the streets, are
you recognized?

252
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Belê. Em çi kewar ne... em tên nas kirin... Em cilê xwe em
her nakin... êşera wa ne, ya efrîn in ne.
 
Yes. No matter where we are... we are recognized... We don't
take off our clothes... whether from Şêrewa or from Afrin.

253
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,000
Te jî xwe kirî.
 
You're wearing it too.

254
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:37,000
Min jî xwe kiriye. Ez tim lî xwe dikim. Ez danîn in... e
ciwiyê wê de li xwe dikim.
 
I'm wearing it too. I always wear it. I put it on... I wear
it on the inside.

255
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,000
Başe sê tê ra.
 
Very well.

256
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,000
Mala ava bibe.
 
Thank you.

257
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,000
Seta we xwaş.
 
Bless you.

258
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:45,000
Ka ez kanî me ji... dişêwiran serê me, hani... Bûk e,
daxwazên bûk e... bêj.
 
So I'm thinking... we were talking about this earlier... The
bride, the requests of the bride... tell us.

259
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,000
Ha tu stranê daxwazê dibêje?
 
Ah, you mean you want me to sing a song?

260
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,000
Erê. Ka kerem ke. Bûkê çawa hinê dikin.
 
Yes. Go ahead. How they apply henna on the bride.

261
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,000
Arê.
 
Yeah.

262
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Kerem ke.
 
Please, go ahead.

263
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,000
(Woman singing)
 
(Woman singing)

264
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:55,000
Ha wele hênê... de teşteke...
 
Oh, the henna... it's in a bowl...

265
00:16:55,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Hênê, vî teşteke... ha wele vebke bi çeleke...
 
Henna, in this bowl... oh open it with a piece of cloth...

266
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:06,000
O vebke bi çeleke... Wele da şilingê vebûke kin...
 
Oh open it with a cloth... Oh put it on the bride's
fingers...

267
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:09,000
Da şilingê vebûke kin...
 
Put it on the bride's fingers...

268
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Ha wele em hatin, ji bilbilê...
 
Oh we came from the nightingale...

269
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,000
O, em hatin, ji bilbilê...
 
Oh, we came from the nightingale...

270
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:18,000
Wele mespe xwa grêda bi dergûlê...
 
We tied our faces with flowers...

271
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,000
Mespe xwa grêda bi dergûlê...
 
We tied our faces with flowers...

272
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:25,000
Wele zava na le rûh el mehlê...
 
Oh the groom is in the neighborhood...

273
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,000
Jî me da xaza we çave veklê...
 
He is waiting for us with his eyes...

274
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Seata wa xwaş.
 
Bless you all.

275
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:50,000
(Music playing)
 
(Music playing)

276
00:17:54,000 --> 00:18:00,000
Li rojavayê Kurdistanê, Efrîn, li kêleka Efrînê gundê Kafir
nebû, û gundê Birc Heyder e.
 
In Western Kurdistan, Afrin, next to Afrin is the village of
Kafirnebu, and the village of Birc Heyder.

277
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:05,000
Li Başûr, navçeya Piling, li herêma Samanê û gundê Basofanê.
 
In the South, Piling district, in the Saman region and the
village of Basofan.

278
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:10,000
Li rojava navçeya Asa û gundê Xezawiyê.
 
In the West, Asa district and the village of Xezawiyê.

279
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:15,000
Li Bakur, navçeya Qertel, gundê Birc Ebdalo û Beradê
dikevin.
 
In the North, Qertel district, the villages of Birc Ebdalo
and Berade are located.

280
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:22,000
Navçeya Qertel li binê gund e, ji aliyê Bakur ve tê de gelek
şikevtên kevnar hene.
 
The Qertel district is below the village, from the North
side there are many ancient caves in it.

281
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:25,000
Derdorên gund hemû bi kevir û zinar in.
 
The surroundings of the village are all rocks and boulders.

282
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:30,000
Gihayê çîyayî yên çandinîyê tê re ne hiştine.
 
They haven't left any mountain grass for farming.

283
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:50,000
(Music continues)
 
(Music continues)

284
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,000
Xalo... derbas be. Merheba.
 
Uncle... come in. Hello.

285
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,000
Ehlen wa sehlen, ser çavan. Ehlen wa sehlen.
 
Welcome, you are very welcome. Welcome.

286
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:16,000
Merheba. Çawanî...
 
Hello. How are you...

287
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:22,000
Bixêr hatî. Ser çavan... Merheba xalo. Ahla w sahla. Kerem
kin...
 
Welcome. Very welcome... Hello uncle. Welcome. Please, come
in...

288
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,000
Em e destpêkê xwe bidin nas kirin. Navê we bi xêr?
 
Let's introduce ourselves first. Your name, please?

289
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Henanê Mîlo me, nasnav Erebim.
 
I am Hanan Milo, nicknamed Erebim.

290
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,000
Ê ser çavan apê Henan. Em te jî nas bikin?
 
Welcome Uncle Hanan. Shall we get to know you too?

291
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:32,000
Ez Elîyê Mûsa, Erebê Berkatê Xerîb im.
 
I am Ali Musa, the Arab of Berkatê Xerîb.

292
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,000
Ser çavan yan.
 
Welcome.

293
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:41,000
Dê gund da, gundê we da, bes tu we kir me. Me jî meraq kir
em derbasî dîwana we bin.
 
In the village, your village, you invited us. We were
curious to visit your gathering space.

294
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:46,000
Me li vir xwestiye, em behsa gundê berê bikin, çawa bûn?
 
We wanted to talk about the old villages here, how were
they?

295
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,000
Hûn yekî we xwedan wîcaq e jî.
 
You are one of the owners of the lineage here too.

296
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

297
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,000
Ê bi kurtî xwe bidin nas kirin yanî.
 
So introduce yourselves briefly.

298
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:55,000
Em... mala Berkatê Xerîb in...
 
We... are the family of Berkat the stranger...

299
00:19:55,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Gundên dora me Menozt e, eqiçkê ye, xelîlkê ye...
 
The villages around us are Menozt, Eqiçke, Xelilke...

300
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:07,000
...zarok bi xwe diçin cemayê, em dest û rûyê xwe lê dişon,
bi îzna Xwedê rehet dibin, rind dibin.
 
...children go to the jama, we wash our hands and faces
there, God willing they feel better and heal.

301
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Yanî dema zarokek bêkêf dibe, nexweş dibe, têne cemayê.
 
So when a child is feeling unwell, or sick, they come to the
jama.

302
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Têne cemayê erê, ê heye serê binî mehekê diçe ku tê, diçin
cemayê.
 
They come to the jama yes, some come exactly at the start of
the month, they go to the jama.

303
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:20,000
Ê heye pirsgirêka xwe çêdibe, dîsa diçin cemayê bi îzna
xwedê rehet dibe.
 
Some have a problem, they still go to the jama, and God
willing they heal.

304
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,000
Ê kîjan rojê bi taybetî, an kîjan roj e do?
 
Which specific day do they go to the jama? Which day is it?

305
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:27,000
Heval bi xwedê bi taybetî e xase ku rojên çarşemê ye.
 
My friend, I swear to God, specifically, strictly, it's on a
Wednesday.

306
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:32,000
Çarşemê... vana ev isbata dîna me ye.
 
Wednesday... these are the proofs of our religion.

307
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:36,000
Û vana, hewa dîna me, dîroka dîna me ye.
 
And these, our religion, is the history of our religion.

308
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:40,000
Em bi dîroka xwe razî ne û em bi dîna xwe razî ne.
 
We are content with our history and we are content with our
religion.

309
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:44,000
Û em Xwedan Ocax in, ji bav û kalê me de.
 
And we are the Owners of the Hearth, from our ancestors.

310
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:48,000
Ji hezar salan de... ocaxa me pênc hezar sal de...
 
For thousands of years... our hearth for five thousand
years...

311
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:52,000
...destpêka dinyayê de, em miletê Êzdahî in.
 
...since the beginning of the world, we are the Yezidi
people.

312
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:56,000
Yanî bi taybetî kî nexweş dibe diçe cemayê yanî.
 
Meaning specifically, when someone gets sick, they go to the
jama.

313
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:59,000
Heval, zarokek biçûk bi serê binê mehê de ket...
 
My friend, small children, at the exact beginning of the
month...

314
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:04,000
...dihatin cemayê. Însanê kor, bi korî dihat...
 
...they would come to the jama. A blind person would come
blind...

315
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:09,000
...bi çavan diçû. Însanekî cinik, dihat cemayê...
 
...and leave seeing. A possessed person, would come to the
jama...

316
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:17,000
...bi aqil dibû û diçû mala xwe. Û vana isbata me li Şêrawa
û ev herêma giştî de hene.
 
...regain their sanity and go home. And this is our proof in
Sherawa and this entire area.

317
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,000
Mezinê we kî ne?
 
Who are your leaders?

318
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:23,000
Mezinên me Mala Nabo ye û Mala Şêx Mend e...
 
Our leaders are the Nabo family and the Sheikh Mend
family...

319
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,000
...û mala Nasirdîn e.
 
...and the Nasirdin family.

320
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:29,000
An bi taybet kîjan gundên navên wan meriyên we ne?
 
Specifically, which villages contain your relatives?

321
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:36,000
Ji mariyên me, heqê me di gundê B'iyê, meriyên me ne.
 
From our relatives, the people with rights in B'iye village
are our relatives.

322
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:42,000
Em pismamê hev in, em meriyên hev in. Û Bozfan...
 
We are cousins, we are relatives. And Bozfan...

323
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:46,000
...ev berî dîroka Bozfan û Bêriyê ye. Û Qîbar meriyên me ne.
 
...this is before the history of Bozfan and Beriye. And
Qibar are our relatives.

324
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:50,000
Û wê Feqîra meriyên me ne, Şadêrê meriyên me ne.
 
And Feqira are our relatives, Shadere are our relatives.

325
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:57,000
Îska merovê me tê de hene. Xezêwê merovê me tê de hene.
Qestelê merovê me tê de hene.
 
We have relatives in Iska. We have relatives in Xezewe. We
have relatives in Qestel.

326
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:00,000
Yanî miletê me yê Êzdahî hemî merivên we ne di vê deverê de.
 
So, all the Yezidi people in this area are your relatives.

327
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:05,000
Gelek gundên me li vir ji... berî hemî Êzdahî bûn na... anha
mibislman.
 
Many of our villages here... were all Yezidi before right...
now they're Muslim.

328
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:11,000
Wekî gundê mezin... navê wê Berçqasê... û ev jî miletê me
êzidahî bûne, anha bûn misilman.
 
Like the large village... named Burj Qase... our people
there were Yezidi, now they've become Muslim.

329
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:14,000
Heval, heta na ko tu ko... çiqas Şêrewa de gund heye...
 
My friend, as you asked... however many villages there are
in Sherawa...

330
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:17,000
...dîrokê da wa gişt mêh... giş Êzidî bûn.
 
...in history they were all... they were all Yezidi.

331
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:24,000
Di bin hukmê Ereban de, di bin zorê de fitilîn... û îslam
bûn.
 
Under the rule of the Arabs, by force they turned... and
became Muslims.

332
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,000
Li Birçqasê...
 
In Burj Qase...

333
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:29,000
...li Fafertînê, li Biçxederê, li Kibêşînê.
 
...in Fafertin, in Bichxeder, in Kibeshin.

334
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:34,000
Heta niha zikê melîkê me li wêrê nave xwe Xatûn e, li
Kibêşînê.
 
Until now, the resting place of our queen is there, her name
is Xatun, in Kibeshin.

335
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:39,000
Ev dîroka xwe êzdahî bû. Şêrawa gî êzidahî bû. Ewe bisilman
tê tunebûn heval.
 
Historically, they were Yezidi. All of Sherawa was Yezidi.
There were no Muslims, my friend.

336
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:43,000
Gelek gundê me dî hene anî ta Çelekê jê hene?
 
We have many other villages as well, down to Cheleke too?

337
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:47,000
Pir in heval. Ta bi Çelekê hene û gîşk hene.
 
There are many, my friend. Down to Cheleke and all around.

338
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:53,000
Wekî em bêjin e li vir dî Dêmira... li wê hene kifrê Sifrê
da hene...
 
Like let's say here in Demira... there are some in Kifre
Sifre...

339
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:59,000
...we ki gundê Tace çilî ma naka de hene û isbatê me hene û
dîroka me hene.
 
...like the village of Tace down to our current area, we
have proofs and history.

340
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,000
Gelek ...
 
Many...

341
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:09,000
E buha îzaa ereba hat el kifr nabo ev îzaa kifrê ko ew we...
 
At that time, the Arab radio came, El Kifr Nabo, this
broadcast in Kifre said this...

342
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:16,000
...ev dîroka Zeradeşt e, Kifir Nabo asasê êzidahî ye û
dîroka me ye.
 
...this traces back to Zoroastrian history, Kifir Nabo is
the foundation of Yezidism and our history.

343
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:20,000
Belê dema mirov derbasî Şêrawa dibe dî hemî deran de
nexşeyên kurdan tê de hene.
 
Yes, when you enter Sherawa, there are Kurdish markings
everywhere.

344
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:29,000
Tausî melekê ev ruyê... ev qasek jê nexşê kurdan tê de hene.
ev dîrokek ki... dîrokeke berî hezar sala yan.
 
The Peacock Angel on the walls... there are quite a few
Kurdish symbols. This history... this history goes back
thousands of years.

345
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,000
Heval bi xwda...
 
My friend, by God...

346
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:37,000
...li vê derê Kimarê, kenîsek heye naha hazır a li wir...
Sûreta rojê...
 
...here in the Kimare area, there's a church, it's right
there now... the image of the sun...

347
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:45,000
...û sûreta tawsi î lê ye. Li kevir nexşandine. Û heta niha
mina nîv rojê çû ma sûret kêşanê.
 
...and the image of the peacock is there. Engraved on the
stone. And even recently, I went in the middle of the day to
take a picture of it.

348
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:49,000
Belê me gelek... bi çavê xwe dîtine ev asasê we ye.
 
Yes, we have seen it many times... with our own eyes, this
is your foundation.

349
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Raste... ne ev behsa zaroka kir we got zarok tên cema, kamê
çinê de e kanin bi çikin a zarokan em kanin nîşan didin.
 
Right... so going back to the topic of children going to the
jama, how do you heal the children, can we show it?

350
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,000
E... li wan kanin wi...
 
Yes... you can...

351
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:01,000
Am kanin nwî nîşan (biweşînin)
 
Can we broadcast this?

352
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:04,000
Kanê wenin va zorik.
 
Can you bring the child.

353
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,000
Em naha wek e girin. (Em ê niha vira binin)
 
We will bring him here now.

354
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:19,000
Ya bi navê xwedê... Ya qedana di nê...
 
In the name of God... O Lord of the world...

355
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:22,000
Li aniyê, û lê zik?
 
On the forehead and the stomach?

356
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,000
Erê...
 
Yes...

357
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:25,000
Tu çêdikî naha?
 
What are you doing now?

358
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:28,000
Destê rast û çep... avê rûnî dimê de dest...
 
On the right and left hands... water sits in the hands...

359
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:41,000
Em b'vî tonê re... em wa digirin.
 
We do it with this mud... we hold it like this.

360
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:45,000
Xwedê lê were rehmê e. xwedê şifayek xaliqi bida..
 
May God grant mercy. May God, the Creator, bring healing...

361
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:47,000
Çar aliyan, yanî çar ...
 
To the four sides, meaning the four...

362
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:50,000
Çar qiblî de ye. Heq e.
 
The four directions. It's the truth.

363
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:53,000
Av ev şeklê em ew dest digirin.
 
Like water, we hold this form.

364
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:58,000
Ewa jê nişane kurda ya a vaji evkav evn a..
 
This is also a Kurdish symbol, these moments right here...

365
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:00,000
Bivêrengî zarok di ma naxwaş dakewin ti ne ce mawa ...
 
So this is how children, when they fall ill, they bring them
to your jama...

366
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:07,000
Ê we em tîne cem... em va digrin û çê dibe ... ku qaçêk sêr
de ... sebê, we di caro di rojan ... di xelke di rojan...
 
Yes we bring them to the jama... we hold them and it works
... put a little on the head ... tomorrow, and for two days
... for two days...

367
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,000
çê dibe... rehet dibe.
 
they get better... they heal.

368
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:14,000
rehet dibe, i hê haye di waka va ro ... va gade carek a
rehet deba .. em care din çêdekin wî xwade dê le tî rêhmê u
rehet da ba..
 
they feel better, sometimes right away ... they get better
immediately .. we do it again and God shows mercy and they
heal..

369
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:18,000
Û çi dibêjin we çaxe, gava zoarek tê cem wa dua kî na kin.
 
And what do you say then, when a child comes to you, don't
you say a prayer.

370
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:24,000
Haval de bê wî çaxê em ... ban e oceqê xwa diken. ocax e
bawê kal e xwa diken
 
My friend, at that time we... call upon our hearth. We call
upon the hearth of our ancestors.

371
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:28,000
U em navê xwade ... rebel alemîn ocax e xwa lî da zikr
dakenin ...
 
And in the name of God... the Lord of the Worlds, we invoke
our hearth...

372
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:33,000
em ê taba nav e .. amin amîn .. tebarek a dîn ale em exsen
xaliqin
 
we say the name.. Amen Amen.. blessed faith, Allah the best
of creators

373
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:38,000
oja ta masî ... sedcad dîn ma mad din ... ba ba dîn ,
şexşems qawete dîn
 
our hearth... Suja' al-Din, Mamad Din... Baba Din, Sheikh
Shams the strength of religion

374
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:44,000
