Cheese, these are our things, this is it, everything in the
spring.

499
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:01,000
Yanî penêr a di biharê de çêdikî.
 
So you make the cheese in the spring.

500
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:06,000
Em di biharê de penêrê xwe çêdikin. Meha evwalê biharê em a
penêr çêdikin, penêrê me yê teze we ye.
 
We make our cheese in the spring. In the first month of
spring we make cheese, it's our fresh cheese.

501
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:09,000
Û di biharê xweş e, paşî erd bibe... ev mez çêdikin.
 
And in the spring it's good, then the earth becomes... we
make these raisins.

502
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:14,000
Mez çêdikin, dikelînin, em yê dikin... têkin qetramîza ...
 
We make yogurt, we boil it, we will put it... put it in
jars...

503
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Û lorkê xwe çêdikin. Rûnê xwe çêdikin. Tiştê xwe gişî
çêdikin.
 
And we make our lor. We make our butter. We make all our
things.

504
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:20,000
Naha di payîzê de bes lork ew çêdibin?
 
Now in the autumn is it just lor that are made?

505
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:26,000
Gulîlik çêdibin. Di payîzê biharê em a penêr çêdikin. Naha
em yê gulîlik çêdikin.
 
Guliliks are made. In the autumn and spring we make cheese.
Now we are making guliliks.

506
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:28,000
Naha bes dema gulîlika ye?
 
Is it just the time for guliliks now?

507
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:30,000
Naha bes dema gulîlika... mastê kemonê...
 
Now it's just the time for guliliks... cumin yogurt...

508
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:35,000
Dema ev çêdikî. Kîngê ji te ser wî gulîlikê deng ev çawa
çêdikin?
 
When you make this. Tell me about the guliliks, how do they
make them?

509
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:44,000
Na me... em şîr dikelînin. Û em dimeyînin. Û em berdin kîsê
xwe.
 
Well... we boil milk. And we ferment it. And we pour it into
our bags.

510
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:52,000
Wê bibe nişîve, hinekî am ê dînin... şilvîne. Em derxin wî
çêkin wek pîşika... hûrkin... sor kin wilo.
 
It will set, we will put it down a bit... it will get wet.
We take it out and make it like small pieces... chop it...
fry it like that.

511
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:57,000
Paşî rabin teqin qetramîzek wek zêde xa lê kin. Û em
zivistanî bixwin mûnetê xa ye.
 
Then put it in a jar like putting more on it. And we eat our
provisions in winter.

512
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:58,000
Na ev pêşiya me ye?
 
Now is this in front of us?

513
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,000
He.
 
Yes.

514
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:03,000
Ev wekî wilo çêkirin... teqek wilo çêkin zeytû dike ser.
 
It is made like this... you pop it like that and pour oil
over it.

515
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:05,000
Ev wilo wekî teqê nî wilo teqê dikanin xwar.
 
It's like this, like a pop, you can put it down like a pop.

516
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:08,000
Ev kinc ê we çêkir... di xurt e wilo ev... em çêdikî...
zeytê dikin ser naha dîsa em dikin ... zarokê min daxwaz ...
 
These clothes we made... it is strong like this... we make
it... we put oil on it, now we again... my children
request...

517
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:12,000
Destê te saet xweş be em we dîsa ser we din. Em dî daye
merheba dayê.
 
May your hands have a good time, we will come back to you
again. Hello to the other mother.

518
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:13,000
Ehlaw sehlaw we dî.
 
Welcome to you.

519
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:14,000
Dayê naha te dî şîr e wa.
 
Mother, now you see the milk there.

520
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:15,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

521
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:20,000
Dema tu dibê şîr e wa... ama penêr û rûn û lorke ev hemî
j'vê dar çavê me re ye.
 
When you say it's milk... but cheese and butter and lor,
these are all before our eyes.

522
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:21,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

523
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:24,000
Ji ber ku şîrewe pirraniya wê xwedan pez in.
 
Because mostly those who have milk have sheep.

524
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:25,000
Xwedan çêlek in.
 
They have cows.

525
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:28,000
Xwedan çêlek in. Xwedan pez in... xwedî çêlek in, eh...
 
They have cows. They have sheep... they own cows, yeah...

526
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:29,000
Eh, belê.
 
Yeah, yes.

527
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:32,000
Qanî ji me ra ser wî tiştî ... ew tiştan ... yanî te ser de
dike.
 
Tell us about that thing... those things... I mean, you put
on top.

528
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:35,000
Yanî ez dest pê dikim?
 
I mean, should I start?

529
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

530
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:43,000
Ê manga we yê bizê, ew walede heywan e. Em yê radibin ji
xwar da tîmar dikin.
 
The cow will give birth, it is animal birth. We will get up
from down and tend to them.

531
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:49,000
Em yê ji xwar da bidoşin, me'nî qîçkên xwe. Em şîrê xwe
bikelînin. Mastê xwe bikelînin, em ê berdin pêş.
 
We will milk them from down, meaning for our little ones. We
boil our milk. We boil our yogurt, we will put it in front.

532
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:54,000
Em yê ra bin ji pêş kîş kin... em ev gulîk kin. Mastê
zivistanê bikin.
 
We will get up and serve... we will make this gulik. Make
the winter yogurt.

533
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:59,000
Em diftilin. Biharê am ê dîsan çêleyê we bidoşin. Em şîrê
xwe derman kin.
 
We spin. In the spring we will milk the cows again. We will
treat our milk.

534
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:05,000
Em biftilin xware têkin qac û am e penêrê xwe bikilînin
têkin qîzê.
 
We spin down, put it in containers, and boil our cheese and
put it in the jar.

535
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:08,000
Û eme sîrevkê xwe çêkin em ser kin.
 
And we make our garlic water and pour it over.

536
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:11,000
Me'niya mûnetê qîçikên xwe zivistanê yanî.
 
Meaning winter provisions for our little ones.

537
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:14,000
Naha çi diçe we çêdikin, ko ev hemî ji me re beje.
 
Now what do you make, tell us all this.

538
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,000
Karê hemiyan ez we ra bejim!
 
I will tell you about all the work!

539
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:18,000
Naha we dest bi çi yê ku şîrê ...
 
Now you started with milk ...

540
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:24,000
Paşê biftiline. Em ê penêr çêkin... am mastê xa çêkin am dî
xa rûnê xa çêkin em lorkê xa bigirin.
 
Then it turns. We will make cheese... make our yogurt, we
will also make our butter and take our lor.

541
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:29,000
Ev tiştên me'nî mûnete zivistanê me me zarokên xa am
d'gûrin.
 
These are meaning winter provisions, we keep our children.

542
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:36,000
Û ev sîrek... te bi dev dirêj kir hebû... carek we dî ji wan
sîrikan çêkirin.
 
And this garlic... you talked for a long time... once you
also made some of those garlic things.

543
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:37,000
Êh...
 
Yes...

544
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:38,000
Naha ev sîrik çênakin.
 
Now they don't make these garlic things.

545
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:40,000
Em wan sîrikan çênakin a.
 
We don't make those garlic things.

546
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,000
Na.
 
No.

547
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:45,000
Em bes... em tînin pîşika xwe... têkin qetramîzên xwe... am
masta xwe dikelînin em dikelin.
 
We just... we bring our small pieces... we put them in our
jars... we boil our yogurt, we boil it.

548
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:51,000
Û eme mûneta xwa me'nî qîçikên xuya, zerokên xuya zistanê em
derdixin. Em narin ti deran.
 
And we put out our provisions meaning for our little ones,
our children in the winter. We don't go anywhere.

549
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:54,000
Em a ji te jî bipirsin.
 
Let's ask you too.

550
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,000
Kerem bike.
 
Go ahead.

551
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,000
Xwestek ku hûn hat in we ehlen we sehlen.
 
You came, you are welcome.

552
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:59,000
Silava me ji gişan de hen e.
 
We have greetings for everyone.

553
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:07,000
Xwestek ka we hinekî li ser... xebitbûna gund ... û jin...
dema çawa berê da... alîkar bûn?
 
Please talk a little about... village work... and women...
when how in the past... they were helpers?

554
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:10,000
Eway... eway beriya pêk re...
 
Well... well before that...

555
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:18,000
Eva çend malbûn... dewarê xwe hebûn. Pezê reş hebûn. Pezê
gewre hebûn, mange hebûn. Bi xwe re ew dikirin.
 
There were a few families... they had cattle. They had black
sheep. They had big sheep, they had cows. They did this
themselves.

556
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:22,000
Di biharê da şîrê xwe bi hev re alîkar dikirin.
 
In the spring they helped each other with their milk.

557
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:26,000
Çi dikirin li berbanok da radibûn. Şîrê xwe dikelandin.
 
What were they doing, they woke up at dawn. They boiled
their milk.

558
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:29,000
Bi hev re... te dibêjin bi hev re... cuda nedikrin xelkê
bihevre...
 
Together... you say together... the people didn't do it
separately...

559
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:34,000
Ne didan... heftiyê... îro dora te ye, îro dora me ye. Îro
dora min e. Îro dora wî ye... didan hev.
 
No, they gave... weekly... today is your turn, today is our
turn. Today is my turn. Today is his turn... they did it
together.

560
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:36,000
Şîrê xwe bi hev re alîkar dikirin.
 
They helped each other with their milk.

561
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:38,000
Û dade penêr çawa? Dîsa dev dibo alî hev de jin?
 
And then what about the cheese? Did women help each other
again?

562
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:43,000
Na ev hefte yê min e. Ev hefteya din yê we ye.
 
No, this week is mine. The next week is yours.

563
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:47,000
Erê dî mistafe dikirî. Dema navê vê malekê da penêrê xa
çêbike.
 
Yes they did this. When a house made its cheese.

564
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:50,000
Ew jin ev tên ev bi alîkar in?
 
Did those women come and help?

565
00:37:50,000 --> 00:38:00,000
Wile erê alî hev dikirin ewa naha we qîçkên da pal e...
dihatin wan hev dikirin... ewa şîrê dewarê xwe xweş zehmet
e.
 
Yes, by God, they helped each other. Now in the middle of
this... they came and helped... this milk of their cattle
requires difficulty.

566
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:08,000
Ê dikir penêr de, dikir berê xurcikê, meya hebûn û... dewarê
xwe bi hev dihat, dekalî xwe çê dikir ber bi rûn de.
 
They made cheese, put it in bags, there was fermentation...
and their cattle came together, they boiled it and turned it
to oil.

567
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:18,000
We de çû Halebê... wa bifirota we mûneta mala xwe de kirra
pênca wereqa... sê wereqa. Herti derdikevi de rûbîya qata we
mala da çû.
 
They went to Aleppo... sold it and bought the winter
provisions for the house for fifty notes... three notes.
Every time they went they put the layers together and went
home.

568
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:24,000
Wa we dî raste firoti we mûneta mala dîn bera, em e şeti de
bir e... em re... tiştek dî rinda tînin.
 
And they really sold it and brought the house's provisions
before, we... cut it... we... got good things.

569
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:31,000
E tiştek nî naha rîk hene arebe hene ew nakok xwe dibe ereba
wan wî.
 
Something is not like now, there are roads, there are cars,
they don't carry it, their cars take it.

570
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:35,000
Ev rîkan a berê de meş diçûn Halebê ka wî ku dera da çûn
ku... be xa dîşiyan.
 
These roads, in the past they walked to Aleppo, where did
they go... they suffered.

571
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:37,000
Naha gundê we... gundê musilman hene, îzidî hen e.
 
Now your village... there are Muslim villages, there are
Yezidi ones.

572
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:40,000
Hene zerdeştin. Hene musilman a.
 
There are Zardashti. There are Muslims.

573
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:47,000
Ha bo te ew dî de we da tê ferqa tena... ev de av dî de
alîkar de bûn e, bi mûneta xwe we ew çêdikin...
 
There was no difference for you... they helped each other...
they made provisions...

574
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:52,000
de fê ew nan de dan e ew de kin her hevde nan didan hevde...
cîwa tê ferqek tunebû ji me...
 
they gave bread... we helped each other, gave bread to each
other... there was no difference among us...

575
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:55,000
Û ev xezwê we yî berê şiko danî?
 
And how did this old bond start?

576
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:59,000
Me gaziweya kehnê hebû, ma dewanê we xwe de birin didoştin.
 
We had old gas lamps, we brought our cattle and milked.

577
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:03,000
Zehmet bo di seri yekan e wena, cî gazawe cî...
 
It was difficult on one another, we had gas lamps...

578
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,000
Wileh heye we...
 
By God, yes...

579
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:05,000
Zehmet bû... kaş bû?
 
Was it difficult... was it a struggle?

580
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:12,000
Zehmet bu wela... kaş bu em dewarê xwe dibirin cî ran a halê
xirab bû da yîk a me wê av û tiştkî tanîn.
 
It was difficult, by God... it was a struggle, we took our
carts to places, it was a bad state, our mothers brought
water and things.

581
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:22,000
Wê dihatin dapîran e... wê xa dixulan pe firaq xa d'şûşti,
pe cil xa d'şûşt i cî e, halê rezîl di ber bang da radibûn
feqîra... dewar re... av didan.
 
They came, the grandmothers... they spun it, washed the
dishes, washed the clothes, it was a terrible state, the
poor ones woke up at dawn... they gave water... to the
cattle.

582
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:28,000
Wê di çûn çolan cerna nîna, kal bar dikirin birçî di bin
çolê de.
 
They went to the plains to graze, the old ones carried loads
hungry in the plains.

583
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:33,000
Noko sehinckê hen e... do kel ê bîre kûlane kûlan e, ava
dere dîx in.
 
Now there are refrigerators... there are two wells here,
they pour water.

584
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:40,000
Zehmet pê pirr bo... a le de yek o ne ser ce de bun sar dey
ka bu.
 
It was very difficult... for the mothers...

585
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:45,000
Kalê we ko ze dayîka bû, şîr mast wê dibin we Haleb be meş.
 
The old ones with the mothers, they went to Aleppo on foot
with the yogurt.

586
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:47,000
Ereb tu bor Haleb bûn ze kû de dûr e bo?
 
Was the car to Aleppo fast, how far was it?

587
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:55,000
Gelek e dûr bo, de m'şîn ta ni sibe digîştin Haleb da
firotin, de vegerin hîvarî difitilin.
 
It was very far, they walked until morning to reach Aleppo,
sold it, and returned spinning in the evening.

588
00:39:55,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Zihmate bu ser zilama. Û zehmet bu ser jina wa.
 
It was difficult on the men. And it was difficult on the
women.

589
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,000
...berê bang da radibûn.
 
...they used to wake up before the call to prayer.

590
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:06,000
Berê bang da radibûn. Ji ezanê pê ve karê malê ji xwe
dikirin. Hemû sibehê radibûn nanê xwe, teynek dikirin, nanê
sêlê dikirin.
 
They used to wake up before the call to prayer. After the
azan, they would do the house chores. Every morning they
would wake up and knead their dough, make bread on the sajj.

591
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:11,000
Nanê sêlê evê dikirina? Bang cîranê xwe dikirina werin em
kefa sibê taştê bixwin.
 
They made bread on the sajj, right? They would call the
neighbors to come have breakfast in the morning.

592
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:14,000
Jiyana gundan, bi rastî xweş e. Heta niha xweş e yanî?
 
Village life is truly beautiful. Is it still beautiful now?

593
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:15,000
Xweş e.
 
It is beautiful.

594
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,000
Ew jiyana heta niha xweş e?
 
Is that life still beautiful?

595
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,000
Hîn xweş e, ji bajarî çêtir e.
 
It's still beautiful, it's better than the city.

596
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:19,000
Qenc e. Hûn gundiyan da rûniştine. Tu misilmanî an êzîdî ye?
 
That's good. You live among the villagers. Are you Muslim or
Yazidi?

597
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,000
Em misilman in.
 
We are Muslim.

598
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,000
Kîja we êzîdî ye?
 
Which one of you is Yazidi?

599
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,000
Zerdeştî ye...
 
She is Zoroastrian...

600
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:25,000
Ê Zerdeştî, û kî va? Tu va.
 
Zoroastrian, and who? You.

601
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:30,000
Yanî misilman, êzîdî bi hev re jiyana xwe dikin... Li gundan
jî bawer kim piraniya gundiyan berê êzîdî bûn ne?
 
So Muslims and Yazidis live together... I believe the
majority of the villagers used to be Yazidis in the past,
right?

602
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:33,000
Belê êzîdî jî hebûn, misilman jî hebûn.
 
Yes, there were Yazidis, and there were Muslims.

603
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,000
Ji berê de milet bi hev re jiyan dikir.
 
So, in the past, the people lived together.

604
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:37,000
Belê berê zerdeştî berî me li vî gundî bûn.
 
Yes, in the past, the Zoroastrians were in this village
before us.

605
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:43,000
Û em jî kurmancên Tirkiyê bûn. Berê zulm û zehmetek hebû, em
bi vî awayî derketin.
 
And we were Kurds from Turkey. In the past, there was
oppression and hardship, so we left.

606
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:49,000
Hevalên me yên Zerdeştî... gotin werin, çûn hemû jî li
îskarê rûniştibûn. Gotin werin cem me, em û hûn bi hevdû re
cîran bin.
 
Our Zoroastrian friends... They told us to come, they had
all settled there. They told us to come to them, so we could
be neighbors.

607
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:51,000
Berê me barê arvan dikirin, berê barê arvan bûn.
 
We would load our flour together, in the past, they were
loads of flour.

608
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:57,000
Dibirin aşê dehêran, heta nan dikirin. Ê em ku diçûn Helebê,
qîzên min diwerîn mala te radizan.
 
We would take them to the mill, and even bake bread. And
when we went to Aleppo, my daughters would come and sleep at
your house.

609
00:40:57,000 --> 00:41:00,000
Û hûn ku diçûn Helebê, qîçkên te diwerîn mala min radizan.
 
And when you went to Aleppo, your daughters would come and
sleep at my house.

610
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:05,000
Yanî xweşikiya gundan, bi hev re, alîkarî, û cîrantî ew
mirovantî pir xweş e.
 
So the beauty of the villages, being together, helping each
other, and the neighborliness, the humanity is very
beautiful.

611
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,000
Pir xweş bû, xweş bû berê..
 
It was very beautiful, it was beautiful in the past...

612
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:08,000
Mala we ava be... Xwedê kêmasiya we nede, siheta we xweş.
 
May your home be prosperous... May God not let you lack
anything, bless your health.

613
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:10,000
Ya te jî xweş be.
 
Bless yours too.

614
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:16,000
[Muzîk tê lêxistin]
 
[Music playing]

615
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:18,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja û ezîz.
 
Yes, valuable and dear viewers.

616
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:23,000
Em spasiya we dikin. Heya niha hûn li ber ekranê bûn û we li
me temaşe dikir.
 
We thank you. Until now you were in front of your screens,
and you were watching us.

617
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,000
Li vir em digihîjin dawiya bernameya xwe.
 
Here we reach the end of our program.

618
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:27,000
Bernameya Xwezaya Welat...
 
The "Nature of the Country" program...

619
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:29,000
Heya hefteyeke din em ê dîsa bi hev re bin.
 
We will be together again next week.

620
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:31,000
Îro em li gundê Qibê bûn.
 
Today we were in the village of Qibê.

621
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:33,000
Hefteyeke din em ê li gundekî din bin.
 
Next week we will be in another village.

622
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,000
Bi xatirê we.
 
Goodbye.

623
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:42,000
Weylo delal, weylo delal, weylo delal...
 
Alas my beloved, alas my beloved, alas my beloved...

624
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:48,000
Benda dilê min delal...
 
The tie of my heart, my beloved...

625
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:52,000
Delal bi qurban, bila sibe da xilapî min e...
 
My beloved, I'd be your sacrifice, may the morning trick
me...

626
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:56,000
Har wî kefa çawelîka deşta Cuma ber de sûre...
 
And that joy of the eyes...

627
